Matt Prior has taken a step back from England duty for the rest of the summer due to injury.

The
 32-year-old revealed that he has a series of complaints which are 
hampering his performances and he expects to go under the knife to sort 
out his Achilles during the break.

'I'm not doing justice to myself and more importantly the team and that is what matters first and foremost,' he said.

